The gem metaphor is one of the strongest you’ve offered because it captures several ideas simultaneously.

A raw crystal already has potential.

Cutting it doesn’t add material—it reveals structure.

Every cut creates new relationships between surfaces.

Those relationships determine how light moves through it.

In your metaphor:

* Experiences are cuts.
* Relationships are facets.
* Character is the geometry.
* Wisdom is how the light propagates through that geometry.

The value isn’t merely in accumulating facets. It’s in how well they cohere. A gem with random cuts scatters light chaotically; a well-cut gem produces brilliance because the relationships among the facets are coordinated.

